---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Neighborhood Map
metaDescription: A map of the neighborhoods that make up White Plains, New York.
---
<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="eyebrow">White Plains</p>
    <h1>Neighborhood map</h1>
    <p>A simple map of the neighborhoods that make up White Plains. Use it as a starting point for getting oriented to the city.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <figure
      class="about-photo map-figure"
      id="wpcna-map"
      data-map-w="{{ neighborhoodPolygons.imageWidth }}"
      data-map-h="{{ neighborhoodPolygons.imageHeight }}"
      style="margin:0 auto;max-width:900px;position:relative"
    >
      <img
        src="{{ '/assets/img/neighborhood-map.png' | withPrefix }}"
        alt="Map of White Plains showing neighborhood boundaries and labels."
        loading="eager"
        style="width:100%;height:auto;border-radius:var(--radius-lg);display:block"
      >
      <svg
        class="map-highlight-svg"
        id="wpcna-map-svg"
        viewBox="0 0 {{ neighborhoodPolygons.imageWidth }} {{ neighborhoodPolygons.imageHeight }}"
        preserveAspectRatio="none"
        aria-hidden="true"
      >
        <polygon id="wpcna-map-polygon" points=""></polygon>
      </svg>
      <figcaption id="wpcna-map-caption" style="text-align:center;font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--ink-muted);margin-top:0.75rem">
        Map of White Plains neighborhoods.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <div class="spotlight" style="margin-top:2.5rem">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Explore</p>
        <h2>Browse the neighborhoods</h2>
        <p>WPCNA tracks every named neighborhood across White Plains, from Downtown to the hills on the city's edge. Each one has its own page with photos, history, and what makes it distinct.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:1rem"><a class="btn btn-primary" href="{{ '/neighborhoods/' | withPrefix }}">All neighborhoods</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="spotlight-card">
        <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
        <h3>Why neighborhoods matter</h3>
        <p>Each neighborhood has its own character, concerns, and priorities. WPCNA exists to help those neighborhoods stay connected to each other and to the city.</p>
        <a class="btn btn-outline btn-block" href="{{ '/about/' | withPrefix }}" style="margin-top:0.75rem">About WPCNA</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .map-figure { position: relative; }
  .map-highlight-svg {
    position: absolute;
    left: 0; top: 0;
    width: 100%; height: calc(100% - 0px);
    pointer-events: none;
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
  }
  .map-figure .map-highlight-svg { height: auto; }
  /* Make the SVG overlay stretch to match the image */
  #wpcna-map { position: relative; }
  #wpcna-map img { position: relative; z-index: 0; }
  #wpcna-map .map-highlight-svg {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  #wpcna-map .map-highlight-svg.is-active { opacity: 1; }
  #wpcna-map-polygon {
    fill: rgba(255, 235, 0, 0.32);
    stroke: #ffeb00;
    stroke-width: 12;
    stroke-linejoin: round;
    stroke-linecap: round;
    paint-order: stroke fill;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 3px #000) drop-shadow(0 0 14px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.9));
    animation: wpcna-poly-pulse 2s ease-in-out infinite;
  }
  @keyframes wpcna-poly-pulse {
    0%, 100% { fill-opacity: 0.25; }
    50%      { fill-opacity: 0.50; }
  }
</style>
<script id="wpcna-map-polygons" type="application/json">{{ neighborhoodPolygons.polygons | dump | safe }}</script>
<script>
(function () {
  var fig = document.getElementById('wpcna-map');
  var svg = document.getElementById('wpcna-map-svg');
  var poly = document.getElementById('wpcna-map-polygon');
  var cap = document.getElementById('wpcna-map-caption');
  var dataEl = document.getElementById('wpcna-map-polygons');
  if (!fig || !svg || !poly || !dataEl) return;
  var polygons;
  try { polygons = JSON.parse(dataEl.textContent); } catch (e) { return; }

  var params = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
  var slug = params.get('highlight');
  var hash = (window.location.hash || '').replace('#', '');
  if (!slug && hash) slug = hash;
  if (!slug || !polygons[slug]) return;

  var pts = polygons[slug];
  poly.setAttribute('points', pts.map(function (p) { return p[0] + ',' + p[1]; }).join(' '));
  svg.classList.add('is-active');

  var name = slug.replace(/-/g, ' ').replace(/\b\w/g, function (c) { return c.toUpperCase(); });
  if (cap) cap.textContent = 'Highlighted: ' + name;

  requestAnimationFrame(function () {
    fig.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'center' });
  });
})();
</script>
